    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This E30 M3 is a superlative example of homologation engineering, featuring a pristine S14B23 dual-overhead-cam powerplant with crisp individual throttle bodies and a perfectly timed valvetrain. Power is delivered through a robust Getrag 265 five-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential, both of which operate with zero mechanical play. The chassis retains its original rigidity, showing no signs of subframe fatigue or bushing degradation, ensuring the MacPherson strut and semi-trailing arm suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications. This vehicle is mechanically flawless, with a dry undercarriage, optimal compression across all cylinders, and a surgical throttle response that defines the golden era of naturally aspirated performance.",
